theorem interior_closure_iterate_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) (n : ℕ) :
    Function.iterate (fun S : Set X => interior (closure S)) (n.succ) A =
      interior (closure A) := by
  -- Define the map `f := interior ∘ closure`.
  let f : Set X → Set X := fun S => interior (closure S)
  -- First, we show by induction on `n` that `f^[n.succ] = f`.
  have hiter : Function.iterate f (n.succ) = f := by
    induction n with
    | zero =>
        funext S
        simp [Function.iterate, f]
    | succ n ih =>
        funext S
        simp [Function.iterate, f, ih, Topology.interior_closure_idempotent]
  -- Evaluate the functional equality at `A`.
  simpa [f] using congrArg (fun g : Set X → Set X => g A) hiter

theorem closure_interior_idempotent_six {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A))))))))) =
      closure (interior A) := by
  simp [Topology.closure_interior_idempotent]

theorem P2_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    Topology.P2 (X := X) (∅ : Set X) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P2]
  intro x hx
  cases hx
